[3] Massachusetts (Barnstable County)
Date: Wed 19 Nov 2014
Source: CapeCod.com [edited]
http://www.capecod.com/newscenter/falmouth-students-whooping-cough/


Parents of students who attend Falmouth [Barnstable County, Massachusetts] schools have received written notification about a rash of cases of pertussis, also known as whooping cough. Falmouth Schools Assistant Superintendent Nancy Taylor said that 17 students are currently out of school recuperating from the disease. Taylor said school administrators are in touch almost daily with state officials about the status of the situation at the schools.

In Massachusetts, pertussis is most common among people over 10 years old who have lost the protection they get from childhood vaccines, according to state health officials. All but one of the students who have pertussis were immunized, Taylor said. The treatment is to stay home on antimicrobials for 5 days before returning to school, she said.

