******
[4] Idaho
Date: Wed 19 Nov 2014
Source: KPVI [edited]
http://www.kpvi.com/content/news/local/story/Idaho-Attributes-Increase-in-Pertussis-to-Low/M2FEtvj900SynGy_dNF1Tw.cspx


Health officials in Idaho are attributing the increase in pertussis due to the low vaccination rates in the state. The number of cases in Idaho doubled from January to August 2014 from the same periods in 2012 and 2013.

According to the Idaho Department of Health and Welfare, of the 287 cases diagnosed through August 2014, one infant died.

There have been 31 cases of pertussis in the Pocatello and Idaho Falls area, with the highest number of cases being in Boise, Caldwell and Twin Falls.

